<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-911] Enrich Mediator - Cannot enrich an Attribute value of an Element</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-911</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See the following xml&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;student xmlns=&quot;&quot; gender=&quot;female&quot;&amp;gt;                                    &lt;br/&gt;
     &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;John&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;                                    &lt;br/&gt;
     &amp;lt;age&amp;gt;15&amp;lt;/age&amp;gt;                              &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/student&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If we intend to change the value of the &apos;gender&apos; attribute of the &apos;student&apos; element by setting the Enrich mediator&apos;s target&apos;s xpath expression as &quot;//student/@gender&quot;, it will throw a SynapseException saying &quot;Invalid Target object to be enrich.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
